## Tech stack (do not change without asking)

- Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (`static/`, `templates/`)
- Backend: Python 3 + Flask 3 (`app.py`)
- Database: SQLite via `database.py` (no SQLAlchemy тАФ **no `models.py`**; data layer is `database.py`)
- Bilingual code comments: `# EN:` / `# ZH:` in Python; `/* EN: */` in CSS; `{# EN: ... #}` in templates

## Core features implemented

- Register / login / logout (Werkzeug password hash, Flask `session`)
- Roles: `student` | `teacher` via `@login_required(role=...)`
- **Student:** browse courses, enroll, drop, my courses, grades
- **Teacher:** create / edit / delete own courses, view students, assign grades, **remove student from course**
- **Business rules:** max enrollment per course; no duplicate enrollment (`UNIQUE(student_id, course_id)`); role-based routes; teacher can only modify `teacher_id = self`

